Burger King has been around since 1954. It was founded in 1954 in Jacksonville, Florida by James W. McLamore and David Edgerton in Miami. In the early 21st century, Burger King claimed to have about 14,000 stores in nearly 100 countries. Burger King restaurants mainly focus on flame-broiled fast food burgers. The fans describe Burger King as Good value for money, Good quality, Family-friendly, Tasty, and Everywhere. The first time I tried Burger King was in 6th grade, my friend always bought Burger King and its food looked pretty good. So I decided to try it and their food was very tasty. Its burgers are very good and the dessert that I mostly like is the Hershey's pie they make. The smoothies are also very good and they have many different flavor options. A reason I recommend this restaurant is because their desserts are a delicacy, especially their Hershey’s Pie. Their Hershy’s pie is made with a thin layer of chocolate cookie at the bottom and with a type of chocolate ganache on the top. What makes the Hersheys pie even better is the whipped cream they put at the top of the pie. Also, I recommend this restaurant because their burgers are different from any other, even though Burger King makes some of its burgers from vegetables they taste just as good as the burgers made with real meat. Another reason I recommend this restaurant is because even though their burgers are better than others, they still sell them at a low price compared to how other restaurants sell their burgers. Finally, I recommend this restaurant because their milkshakes are tastier than any other milkshake I have tasted, the ice cream is soft and it isn’t lumpy which makes a normal milkshake even better! I recommend this product to people who like meat because the meat Burger King uses for its burgers is very tasty and soft. Also, I recommend Burger King to people that have a sweet tooth because their desserts, especially their Hershey's pie’s are very good and sweet. Another type of person I recommend Burger King to is those people who love milkshakes because as I have mentioned before the ice cream they use to make these milkshakes is very soft and it doesn’t matter if it’s vanilla or chocolate-flavored, they both taste amazing. Something the potential customers should know before trying this restaurant is that if they do go to Burger King they should 100% try their Hersheys Pie.
